7.3 Types of loop

1. do-while loop

* Syntax:

do {                               do me jvm aayega do ka code execute krega
    // Body of the loop             (1st time chalega hi)
}
while (condition);           ➡️    fir jvm while ki condition ko
                                   check krega agr condition true
                                   hue to wapas do me jayega werna
                                   exit ho jayega

A. Executes block first, then checks condition.
B. Guaranteed to run at least one iteration.
C. Unlike while, first iteration is unconditional.
D. Don't forget to update condition to avoid infinite loops.


2. For-Loop

* Syntax:

for (initialisation; condition; update){
// Body of the loop
}

A. Standard loop for running code multiple times.
B. Generally preferred for counting iterations.

3. For-Each Loop

1. A method for array iteration, often preferred for readability.
2. Parameters: One for item, optional second for index.
3. Using return is similar to continue in traditional loops.
4. Not straightforward to break out of a forEach loop.
5. When you need to perform an action on each array element and
   don't need to break early.
